cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper discusses methods for segmenting fiber bundles in the human brain using DTI data. This involves image processing and analysis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The methods also involve graph theory and optimization, which are areas of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The comparison of segmentation results using a similarity coefficient is a common evaluation metric in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of neuronavigation for neurosurgical interventions involves graphics and visualization (cs.GR).
